title: Dionne Warwick - At Her Very Best [FLAC]
description:
Tracks 1 to 20, from 1962 through 1970, are from the CD "At Her Very Best" (1989)
by Pair Records, a division of Essex Entertainment.

Tracks 21 to 30, from 1967 through 1987, are from other CDs and are included here to make a collection of her significant singles.  Their album title and album cover picture are set to the same as tracks 1 through 20.

I have added track gain adjustment information to each track, so that some music players can play the whole set of tracks with somewhat similar volume.

----------------------------------------------

Tracks from the CD:

01 - I Say A Little Prayer
02 - Walk On By
03 - I’ll Never Fall In Love Again
04 - Anyone Who Had A Heart
05 - Message To Michael
06 - Do You Know The Way To San Jose
07 - Alfie
08 - You’ve Lost That Lovin’ Feeling
09 - Reach Out For Me
10 - Don’t Make Me Over
11 - Trains And Boats And Planes
12 - I Just Don’t Know What To Do With Myself
13 - The Windows Of The World
14 - You’ll Never Get To Heaven (If You Break My Heart)
15 - Make It Easy On Yourself
16 - Are You There (With Another Girl)
17 - A House Is Not A Home
18 - This Girl’s In Love With You
19 - Who’s Gonna Love Me?
20 - Who Can I Turn To

These tracks are from other CDs:

21 - Theme From “Valley Of The Dolls”
22 - (There’s) Always Something There To Remind Me
23 - Promises, Promises
24 - Paper Mache
25 - Then Came You (with The Spinners)
26 - I’ll Never Love This Way Again
27 - Deja Vu
28 - Heartbreaker
29 - That’s What Friends Are For (with Elton John, Gladys Knight & Stevie Wonder)
30 - Love Power (with Jeffrey Osborne)
